4
00:00:43,938 --> 00:00:46,872
[Episode 12]

5
00:00:51,772 --> 00:00:53,672
It's delicious.

6
00:00:53,672 --> 00:00:56,172
Why aren't you eating?

7
00:00:56,172 --> 00:00:57,638
What brings you here?

8
00:00:57,638 --> 00:01:00,038
Are you curious about how I got here?

9
00:01:00,038 --> 00:01:01,438
Not why I came?

10
00:01:01,438 --> 00:01:04,938
It seems my father-in-law
has some grievances against me.

11
00:01:04,938 --> 00:01:07,038
He actually reported me to the police.

12
00:01:07,038 --> 00:01:10,572
I was detained but recently released on bail.

13
00:01:10,572 --> 00:01:11,872
There's no need to be surprised.

14
00:01:11,872 --> 00:01:15,205
Your daughter should also know
the family atmosphere to prepare herself.

15
00:01:15,205 --> 00:01:16,338
What are you doing right now?

16
00:01:16,338 --> 00:01:17,705
I feel upset, Du Jun.

17
00:01:17,705 --> 00:01:20,505
Not even inviting me to this family event?

18
00:01:20,505 --> 00:01:23,005
Oh, am I not considered family?

19
00:01:23,005 --> 00:01:26,972
Is the dead son's wife not family?

20
00:01:29,105 --> 00:01:30,372
I apologize, Madam.

21
00:01:30,372 --> 00:01:33,105
It seems our eldest daughter-in-law
has some misunderstanding.

22
00:01:33,105 --> 00:01:34,338
A misunderstanding?

23
00:01:34,338 --> 00:01:36,005
Hui Won should also know certain things.

24
00:01:36,005 --> 00:01:39,838
That those without blood ties
like us can be cast out anytime.

25
00:01:39,838 --> 00:01:41,572
What are you saying now?

26
00:01:41,572 --> 00:01:43,005
It's a joke.

27
00:01:43,005 --> 00:01:44,405
A joke.

28
00:01:44,405 --> 00:01:47,372
It means anyone who becomes

29
00:01:47,372 --> 00:01:51,305
a daughter-in-law of Taehan Group
must have exceptional resolve.

30
00:01:52,472 --> 00:01:54,305
You understand, right, sister-in-law?

31
00:01:59,972 --> 00:02:01,572
Is resolve really necessary?

32
00:02:01,572 --> 00:02:05,738
I don't want a marriage
built on fear and caution.

33
00:02:05,738 --> 00:02:08,905
Marriage is about love, not resolve.

34
00:02:08,905 --> 00:02:11,005
Two people who've lived differently

35
00:02:11,005 --> 00:02:13,505
accept their differences and adapt,

36
00:02:13,505 --> 00:02:15,905
striving to be happy together.

37
00:02:15,905 --> 00:02:19,205
I believe that's how families are built, too.

38
00:02:19,205 --> 00:02:23,372
Not by blood, but with hearts
that genuinely cherish each other.

39
00:02:25,105 --> 00:02:26,572
You're really innocent.

40
00:02:26,572 --> 00:02:31,272
And that dear family
turned me over to the police?

41
00:02:31,272 --> 00:02:33,338
Sister-in-law, this is the occasion for us

42
00:02:33,338 --> 00:02:37,272
to formally greet each other's parents.

43
00:02:37,272 --> 00:02:40,205
And Hui Won doesn't need
any grand resolutions.

44
00:02:40,205 --> 00:02:41,925
Because she's perfectly fine just as she is.

45
00:02:43,272 --> 00:02:44,572
Please mind your manners.

46
00:02:44,572 --> 00:02:47,138
She's the person I'll spend my life with.

47
00:02:52,072 --> 00:02:53,805
Everyone, cut it out.

48
00:02:59,638 --> 00:03:01,672
I'm the one you should deal with.

49
00:03:01,672 --> 00:03:05,505
Come take a little walk with me, okay?

50
00:03:06,505 --> 00:03:09,172
Madam, I apologize.

51
00:03:24,772 --> 00:03:26,938
I truly apologize again.

52
00:03:49,238 --> 00:03:50,638
Why aren't you saying anything?

53
00:03:50,638 --> 00:03:52,572
Because I feel pity for you.

54
00:03:53,738 --> 00:03:58,005
I feel pity for you even attempting
one last desperate act.

55
00:03:58,005 --> 00:04:02,405
There was a time when you shone brightest
alongside Han Jun in that very spot.

56
00:04:02,405 --> 00:04:03,572
I don't need your charity.

57
00:04:03,572 --> 00:04:05,238
You shouldn't have come here today.

58
00:04:05,238 --> 00:04:06,938
Then where was I supposed to go?

59
00:04:06,938 --> 00:04:08,205
You haven't even answered my calls.

60
00:04:08,205 --> 00:04:09,605
Think about what you've done.

61
00:04:09,605 --> 00:04:12,405
Not appreciating all the times
I forgave your wrongdoings

62
00:04:12,405 --> 00:04:14,238
just because you are Han Jun's wife
and Se Hyeon's mother.

63
00:04:14,238 --> 00:04:18,272
Why can't you see that you're
the one who betrayed our family?

64
00:04:18,272 --> 00:04:20,072
That position was originally mine.

65
00:04:20,072 --> 00:04:22,872
I'm just trying to reclaim
what belongs to me and Se Hyeon.

66
00:04:22,872 --> 00:04:24,672
It was Du Jun who took it away.

67
00:04:24,672 --> 00:04:28,138
Han Jun, the baby in my womb, everything.

68
00:04:29,238 --> 00:04:31,538
There's no one who doesn't know your pain.

69
00:04:31,538 --> 00:04:35,472
How long will you remain chained to the past?

70
00:04:35,472 --> 00:04:36,938
Don't pretend to care.

71
00:04:36,938 --> 00:04:39,672
It's because of you, Father,
that I became like this.

72
00:04:39,672 --> 00:04:41,038
You were worried that I,

73
00:04:41,038 --> 00:04:42,238
even after losing my husband,

74
00:04:42,238 --> 00:04:44,638
might shamelessly cling to your family

75
00:04:44,638 --> 00:04:46,172
and take over the household

76
00:04:46,172 --> 00:04:48,072
or Du Jun's place.

77
00:04:48,072 --> 00:04:49,572
That's what you were worried about,

78
00:04:49,572 --> 00:04:51,305
isn't it?

79
00:04:59,472 --> 00:05:02,238
So in the end, you're
abandoning me like this?

80
00:05:02,238 --> 00:05:04,472
I won't crumble so easily.

81
00:05:05,138 --> 00:05:08,938
Everyone in this household will regret it!

82
00:05:28,485 --> 00:05:29,605
[Contacts]

83
00:05:33,338 --> 00:05:37,805
The subscriber is unavailable.
You are being redirected to voicemail...

84
00:05:41,772 --> 00:05:43,872
The subscriber is unavailable.

85
00:05:44,672 --> 00:05:46,805
[Director Lee Woo Jin]

86
00:05:51,238 --> 00:05:52,638
Hello, Director.

87
00:05:52,638 --> 00:05:55,105
Director, please listen to me.

88
00:05:55,105 --> 00:05:56,138
I can explain everything.

89
00:05:56,138 --> 00:05:58,672
I know you've already contacted
a lot of people, President Han.

90
00:05:58,672 --> 00:06:00,705
Just a moment, please let me speak first...

91
00:06:00,705 --> 00:06:04,205
We've also received things over time,
so we didn't want to go this far.

92
00:06:04,205 --> 00:06:06,405
But now that the Chairman
even ousted the Vice Chairman,

93
00:06:06,405 --> 00:06:08,772
we have no justification to side with you.

94
00:06:08,772 --> 00:06:09,772
Wait, just a moment.

95
00:06:09,772 --> 00:06:11,105
I have plans for everything.

96
00:06:11,105 --> 00:06:13,505
Probably, no one will
come back to you, President Han.

97
00:06:13,505 --> 00:06:15,538
I thought someone should tell you this.

98
00:06:15,538 --> 00:06:16,638
Hello?

99
00:06:16,638 --> 00:06:18,821
Director? Director!

100
00:06:18,821 --> 00:06:19,909
[Director Lee Woo Jin]

101
00:06:41,872 --> 00:06:44,605
Mom, talk a bit more before leaving.

102
00:06:44,605 --> 00:06:46,172
I know what you're thinking.

103
00:06:46,172 --> 00:06:47,172
What more is there to say?

104
00:06:47,172 --> 00:06:50,072
You knew all about that family, didn't you?

105
00:06:50,072 --> 00:06:51,738
The President did nothing wrong.

106
00:06:51,738 --> 00:06:54,138
He explained everything,
and I understood completely.

107
00:06:54,138 --> 00:06:55,472
Then that's enough.

108
00:06:55,472 --> 00:06:56,905
Huh?

109
00:06:56,905 --> 00:06:58,272
You said you knew.

110
00:06:58,272 --> 00:06:59,938
But you still chose him.

111
00:06:59,938 --> 00:07:02,638
To live together anyway.

112
00:07:02,638 --> 00:07:04,038
That's true, but...

113
00:07:04,038 --> 00:07:08,205
Seeing you today,
I don't need to worry anymore.

114
00:07:09,272 --> 00:07:13,038
Seeing you stand together
against what happened earlier,

115
00:07:14,805 --> 00:07:18,638
I feel like you two will handle
anything that comes your way.

116
00:07:18,638 --> 00:07:20,538
Marriage isn't anything complicated.

117
00:07:20,538 --> 00:07:24,405
Just support each other like today,
and that's how you live.

118
00:07:26,372 --> 00:07:28,272
I couldn't do that,

119
00:07:28,272 --> 00:07:30,338
but you're different from me.

120
00:07:30,338 --> 00:07:32,072
Mom.

121
00:07:34,105 --> 00:07:35,572
Live well.

122
00:07:35,572 --> 00:07:40,572
It's the best gift and revenge

123
00:07:40,572 --> 00:07:42,272
I can give you.

124
00:07:46,138 --> 00:07:47,872
I should go.

125
00:08:08,772 --> 00:08:10,472
You really had a tough day today.

126
00:08:10,472 --> 00:08:12,205
You too, President.

127
00:08:12,205 --> 00:08:14,072
I'll contact your mother directly.

128
00:08:14,072 --> 00:08:15,172
She must be very worried.

129
00:08:15,172 --> 00:08:17,438
Actually, she might not be worried.

130
00:08:17,438 --> 00:08:20,138
- Huh?
- Seeing us protect each other earlier

131
00:08:20,138 --> 00:08:21,572
put her mind at ease.

132
00:08:21,572 --> 00:08:23,338
Isn't that a relief?

133
00:08:23,338 --> 00:08:25,605
That's a relief, but I can't promise

134
00:08:25,605 --> 00:08:28,005
everything will be smooth sailing.

135
00:08:28,005 --> 00:08:29,905
There may be other attacks,

136
00:08:29,905 --> 00:08:32,505
and you might get caught up
in unwanted rumors.

137
00:08:32,505 --> 00:08:34,305
But

138
00:08:34,305 --> 00:08:36,772
I promise you this one thing.

139
00:08:37,605 --> 00:08:39,005
No matter what happens,

140
00:08:39,005 --> 00:08:42,138
I will protect you
unconditionally, to the end.

141
00:08:51,205 --> 00:08:53,445
[How to propose in a way women love]

142
00:08:53,445 --> 00:08:54,505
[Propose ideas]

143
00:08:54,505 --> 00:08:57,381
[How did everyone propose? Public Proposal]

144
00:09:02,738 --> 00:09:06,238
Wait, in this case,
I'm supposed to hold her hand.

145
00:09:07,438 --> 00:09:11,872
Du Jun, the gift set we agreed to supply
to the department store...

146
00:09:11,872 --> 00:09:12,905
- What are you doing?
- Doing what?

147
00:09:12,905 --> 00:09:13,972
Why are you acting like that?

148
00:09:13,972 --> 00:09:15,338
I was just doing a stretch, why?

149
00:09:15,338 --> 00:09:17,005
Ah, terrible acting.

150
00:09:17,005 --> 00:09:18,272
You're acting really suspicious right now.

151
00:09:18,272 --> 00:09:19,272
- Me?
- Yes, you.

152
00:09:19,272 --> 00:09:20,472
- I'm not.
- Yes, you are.

153
00:09:20,472 --> 00:09:22,638
What is it? Tell me, between us.

154
00:09:22,638 --> 00:09:23,938
What were you looking at? What?

155
00:09:23,938 --> 00:09:25,838
No, I'm just a bit sleepy.

156
00:09:25,838 --> 00:09:28,105
Just sleepy.

157
00:09:28,105 --> 00:09:29,238
[How to propose in a way women love]

158
00:09:29,238 --> 00:09:30,272
A proposal?

159
00:09:30,272 --> 00:09:32,105
When, where, how? Did you buy a ring?

160
00:09:32,105 --> 00:09:34,672
I'll have to prepare those things one by one.

161
00:09:34,672 --> 00:09:38,705
If things aren't going well on your own,
try getting help from people

162
00:09:38,705 --> 00:09:40,172
- who are happily married.
- Help?

163
00:09:40,172 --> 00:09:43,405
They might be closer than you think.

164
00:09:50,205 --> 00:09:51,372
Mi Ran!

165
00:09:51,372 --> 00:09:53,372
Huh? Cha Min Uk!

166
00:09:54,405 --> 00:09:57,338
Ta-da! A gift!

167
00:09:57,338 --> 00:09:58,672
- What is it?
- What do you mean what?

168
00:09:58,672 --> 00:09:59,672
It's your side dish container.

169
00:09:59,672 --> 00:10:01,038
I mean,

170
00:10:01,038 --> 00:10:02,138
there's something inside?

171
00:10:02,138 --> 00:10:04,905
Yeah, it's polite to return something
when you receive it.

172
00:10:04,905 --> 00:10:06,738
I put some homemade side dishes inside.

173
00:10:06,738 --> 00:10:07,738
You cooked?

174
00:10:07,738 --> 00:10:09,405
You never cared about cooking before.

175
00:10:09,405 --> 00:10:10,405
- Me?
- Yeah.

176
00:10:10,405 --> 00:10:12,605
No, I'm really good at cooking.

177
00:10:12,605 --> 00:10:14,872
I just haven't done it
because I've been busy.

178
00:10:14,872 --> 00:10:16,438
- I'm good at it.
- Yeah?

179
00:10:16,438 --> 00:10:19,072
I'm actually quick with my hands
and good at household chores.

180
00:10:19,072 --> 00:10:20,197
I'd probably make a great spouse too.

181
00:10:20,197 --> 00:10:22,072
Oh.

182
00:10:22,072 --> 00:10:24,272
Yeah? I didn't know.

183
00:10:24,272 --> 00:10:26,938
Too bad there's no way
to show you this charm of mine.

184
00:10:26,938 --> 00:10:29,772
What a shame, what should I do?

185
00:10:33,838 --> 00:10:36,672
Anyway, I'll enjoy this, thanks.

186
00:10:36,672 --> 00:10:38,838
Hey, aren't you busy? Go on in.

187
00:10:38,838 --> 00:10:41,438
Nope, I told my team leader
I'd be out for a bit, so it's okay.

188
00:10:41,438 --> 00:10:44,005
I can't take up a busy person's time.

189
00:10:44,005 --> 00:10:45,138
This is part of my support too.

190
00:10:45,138 --> 00:10:47,138
- Huh?
- I'm leaving.

191
00:10:47,138 --> 00:10:49,505
- Bye.
- Hey, right...

192
00:10:50,138 --> 00:10:52,272
Go inside.

193
00:10:52,272 --> 00:10:53,972
Okay.

194
00:11:04,238 --> 00:11:06,472
Why is Hwang Mi Ran like this?

195
00:11:08,872 --> 00:11:10,605
What's this?

196
00:11:12,605 --> 00:11:15,238
Thank you for your order, valued customer.

197
00:11:15,238 --> 00:11:16,837
[Gil Soo's Side Dish Shop]

198
00:11:18,053 --> 00:11:19,781
Jeez.

199
00:11:21,205 --> 00:11:23,505
Why are you having lunch now?

200
00:11:23,505 --> 00:11:24,505
What's this?

201
00:11:24,505 --> 00:11:26,738
This isn't ordinary effort.

202
00:11:26,738 --> 00:11:29,438
But what is this?

203
00:11:29,438 --> 00:11:31,938
Is this bought
and packed from a side dish shop?

204
00:11:31,938 --> 00:11:34,205
She'd be really embarrassed if she knew
there was a note like this inside.

205
00:11:34,205 --> 00:11:37,038
The effort is what matters.

206
00:11:37,038 --> 00:11:38,405
Look at this one.

207
00:11:38,405 --> 00:11:39,738
Oh, dear.

208
00:11:39,738 --> 00:11:42,972
What kind of sincerity is this?
Just delivering food isn't considered effort.

209
00:11:42,972 --> 00:11:45,938
Cooking is about the personal touch.

210
00:11:45,938 --> 00:11:47,005
It's just tasty.

211
00:11:47,005 --> 00:11:48,072
She should cook it herself
and give it to you.

212
00:11:48,072 --> 00:11:50,138
- This is from a side dish shop.
- Please, eat.

213
00:11:52,405 --> 00:11:53,472
It's delicious.

214
00:11:53,472 --> 00:11:54,572
What is this?

215
00:11:54,572 --> 00:11:56,305
I don't know.

216
00:12:03,038 --> 00:12:04,738
My boy.

217
00:12:15,072 --> 00:12:16,238
Mom.

218
00:12:16,238 --> 00:12:18,838
Oh, you're back.

219
00:12:23,905 --> 00:12:25,138
What's the occasion?

220
00:12:25,138 --> 00:12:26,805
You invited me to your home.

221
00:12:26,805 --> 00:12:30,005
I received some good tea as a gift,
and I thought you might like it.

222
00:12:30,005 --> 00:12:31,738
Please have some.

223
00:12:33,972 --> 00:12:36,705
Ah, it smells amazing.

224
00:12:36,705 --> 00:12:41,338
By the way, you did properly apologize
to Hui Won's mother, right?

225
00:12:41,338 --> 00:12:44,772
Yes, she said not to worry about it
and asked me to tell you that.

226
00:12:44,772 --> 00:12:46,705
Oh, that's a relief.

227
00:12:46,705 --> 00:12:48,338
I heard from your Dad.

228
00:12:48,338 --> 00:12:51,338
That Jeong Eum did a lot of
terrible things all this time.

229
00:12:51,338 --> 00:12:52,772
You've been through a lot
emotionally too, haven't you?

230
00:12:52,772 --> 00:12:54,005
It's all over now.

231
00:12:54,005 --> 00:12:57,205
There's nothing more
my sister-in-law can do now.

232
00:12:57,205 --> 00:13:00,205
But with Hui Won by your side
at times like this,

233
00:13:00,205 --> 00:13:02,838
I feel so relieved.

234
00:13:02,838 --> 00:13:06,705
I really like Hui Won.

235
00:13:11,805 --> 00:13:13,272
Mom, um...

236
00:13:13,272 --> 00:13:16,105
Do you remember Dad's proposal?

237
00:13:16,105 --> 00:13:17,138
Proposal?

238
00:13:17,138 --> 00:13:18,805
Of course, I remember.

239
00:13:18,805 --> 00:13:22,072
That stiff guy's hands were shaking like this

240
00:13:22,072 --> 00:13:23,372
while he put the ring on my hand.

241
00:13:23,372 --> 00:13:24,905
How could I forget that?

242
00:13:24,905 --> 00:13:27,872
- Dad did that?
- Yes, exactly.

243
00:13:27,872 --> 00:13:29,772
But why bring that up all of a sudden?

244
00:13:29,772 --> 00:13:31,072
Are you planning one too?

245
00:13:31,072 --> 00:13:33,538
Yes, but it's a bit...

246
00:13:35,072 --> 00:13:36,972
Because of your hand?

247
00:13:37,672 --> 00:13:39,538
Is it still difficult?

248
00:13:43,738 --> 00:13:45,738
They say that when someone you love appears,

249
00:13:45,738 --> 00:13:49,305
courage you never imagined comes out.

250
00:13:49,305 --> 00:13:51,105
So you end up doing things you hesitate over.

251
00:13:51,105 --> 00:13:54,138
And you face things you're afraid of.

252
00:13:55,301 --> 00:13:58,405
Have you visited Han Jun's grave?

253
00:13:59,905 --> 00:14:01,272
No, not yet.

254
00:14:01,272 --> 00:14:05,372
When you had worries before,
your brother gave you solutions.

255
00:14:05,372 --> 00:14:07,805
Du Jun, look at me.

256
00:14:07,805 --> 00:14:10,538
It wasn't your fault.

257
00:14:10,538 --> 00:14:14,038
We never blamed you, not once.

258
00:14:14,038 --> 00:14:16,338
So stop now.

259
00:14:18,438 --> 00:14:22,005
Come out of that guilt, okay?

260
00:14:27,272 --> 00:14:30,138
That's what your brother would want too.

261
00:14:33,105 --> 00:14:34,838
Yes.

262
00:14:42,472 --> 00:14:45,472
Okay everyone, attention!

263
00:14:45,472 --> 00:14:48,338
Our Manager Jang won 2nd place in the contest

264
00:14:48,338 --> 00:14:50,272
and got the opportunity
for an internal launch.

265
00:14:50,272 --> 00:14:52,238
Everyone, applause!

266
00:14:52,238 --> 00:14:53,238
Great!

267
00:14:53,238 --> 00:14:55,205
Manager Jang, say a few words.

268
00:14:56,005 --> 00:14:57,138
Thank you.

269
00:14:57,138 --> 00:14:58,638
It really feels like a dream.

270
00:14:58,638 --> 00:15:00,272
My own beer being launched.

271
00:15:00,272 --> 00:15:01,672
I'm so happy for you.

272
00:15:01,672 --> 00:15:03,272
You were trending so much on YouTube.

273
00:15:03,272 --> 00:15:05,038
So the higher-ups recognized your true worth.

274
00:15:05,038 --> 00:15:07,208
Exactly, I've been checking it out
ever since the comments

275
00:15:07,208 --> 00:15:08,938
went absolutely crazy
about non-alcoholic beer!

276
00:15:08,938 --> 00:15:10,338
Exactly! Who are we?

277
00:15:10,338 --> 00:15:11,972
New Product Development Team!

278
00:15:11,972 --> 00:15:13,797
Applause!

279
00:15:13,797 --> 00:15:17,172
- Yes!
- Okay, everyone dismissed.

280
00:15:22,072 --> 00:15:23,905
By the way,

281
00:15:23,905 --> 00:15:25,405
how did he propose to you?

282
00:15:25,405 --> 00:15:27,938
I can't even imagine how extravagant
his proposal must have been.

283
00:15:27,938 --> 00:15:29,005
When's the wedding?

284
00:15:29,005 --> 00:15:30,309
Wait, you don't have the ring?

285
00:15:30,309 --> 00:15:31,505
Oh.

286
00:15:31,505 --> 00:15:33,405
That kind of proposal would embarrass me,

287
00:15:33,405 --> 00:15:35,838
so I'd talk him out of it even if he tried.

288
00:15:35,838 --> 00:15:37,672
What do you mean, that kind of proposal?

289
00:15:37,672 --> 00:15:39,138
It's every woman's fantasy.

290
00:15:39,138 --> 00:15:42,238
Yeah, it's a meaningful event,
so you should accept it.

291
00:15:42,238 --> 00:15:43,938
Manager Nah, how did you propose?

292
00:15:43,938 --> 00:15:46,238
Oh, I proposed by giving her a flower

293
00:15:46,238 --> 00:15:48,638
every day starting 100 days
before the wedding.

294
00:15:48,638 --> 00:15:49,972
My wife absolutely loved it.

295
00:15:49,972 --> 00:15:51,272
She even cried buckets, I tell you.

296
00:15:51,272 --> 00:15:52,972
Oh, is that so?

297
00:15:52,972 --> 00:15:57,105
And that person nearly got in trouble
for forgetting the anniversary and going out?

298
00:15:57,105 --> 00:15:58,672
Why are you bringing that up again?

299
00:15:58,672 --> 00:16:00,005
I brought flowers when I went back.

300
00:16:00,005 --> 00:16:01,305
Oh, I see.

301
00:16:01,305 --> 00:16:02,338
She cried a lot that day too.

302
00:16:02,338 --> 00:16:04,038
- I also...
- Oh, did you?

303
00:16:04,038 --> 00:16:06,105
But she was a bit more angry.

304
00:16:07,605 --> 00:16:09,038
I need to remember next year.

305
00:16:09,038 --> 00:16:10,038
Oh, Mi Ran.

306
00:16:10,038 --> 00:16:13,205
Hey, Jang Hui Won, so you really
wouldn't mind not getting a proposal?

307
00:16:13,205 --> 00:16:14,605
Well,

308
00:16:14,605 --> 00:16:17,038
there are plenty of people
who live happily without that.

309
00:16:17,038 --> 00:16:18,205
No, it's not.

310
00:16:18,205 --> 00:16:20,705
Jang Hui Won, you must have
some expectations, right?

311
00:16:20,705 --> 00:16:21,772
What's there to expect?

312
00:16:21,772 --> 00:16:23,805
I wasn't even thinking
about marriage until recently.

313
00:16:23,805 --> 00:16:24,805
Well, that's true.

314
00:16:24,805 --> 00:16:25,905
Then again,

315
00:16:25,905 --> 00:16:28,938
it doesn't cost anything,
so shall we just imagine it once?

316
00:16:28,938 --> 00:16:30,038
Yeah, tell me.

317
00:16:30,038 --> 00:16:31,705
Well...

318
00:16:31,705 --> 00:16:34,505
At a place with a nice atmosphere,

319
00:16:34,505 --> 00:16:36,838
while we're having a cozy time together,

320
00:16:36,838 --> 00:16:38,672
music suddenly starts playing,

321
00:16:38,672 --> 00:16:39,938
and candles flickering.

322
00:16:39,938 --> 00:16:42,105
Ah, and some balloons would be cute too.

323
00:16:42,105 --> 00:16:43,638
Well, well.

324
00:16:43,638 --> 00:16:46,672
In a place like that,
just like everyone else,

325
00:16:46,672 --> 00:16:47,938
hand over the ring and ask,

326
00:16:47,938 --> 00:16:51,038
'Will you marry me?'

327
00:16:51,038 --> 00:16:53,005
You've imagined this
more than once, haven't you?

328
00:16:53,005 --> 00:16:56,138
No, it's just... words.

329
00:16:56,138 --> 00:16:58,105
You know I don't expect things like that.

330
00:16:58,105 --> 00:17:00,338
Yeah, just like everyone else, ordinary.

331
00:17:00,338 --> 00:17:03,238
- Right.
- It's the simplest thing, yet the hardest.

332
00:17:03,238 --> 00:17:05,338
Anyway, got it. Have a good rest.

333
00:17:05,338 --> 00:17:07,072
Okay.

334
00:17:08,172 --> 00:17:09,905
What is it?

335
00:17:11,605 --> 00:17:12,838
You heard that, right?

336
00:17:12,838 --> 00:17:14,538
'Just ordinary like everyone else.'

337
00:17:14,538 --> 00:17:16,305
That's actually the hardest answer.

338
00:17:16,305 --> 00:17:18,905
Wouldn't it be better
to just ask her directly now?

339
00:17:18,905 --> 00:17:21,638
Then, the charm of the surprise
would be lost.

340
00:17:21,638 --> 00:17:24,438
That's why I'm asking you both for help.

341
00:17:24,438 --> 00:17:28,505
She'll probably feel more comfortable
talking to you than to me.

342
00:17:28,505 --> 00:17:30,638
Here, have some of this.

343
00:17:34,838 --> 00:17:35,838
Got it.

344
00:17:35,838 --> 00:17:37,938
Then let's start by interpreting the word

345
00:17:37,938 --> 00:17:39,672
'ordinary' that Hui Won mentioned.

346
00:17:39,672 --> 00:17:41,638
Exactly, 'ordinary.'

347
00:17:41,638 --> 00:17:44,238
It's one of the most
important moments in life,

348
00:17:44,238 --> 00:17:48,005
so wouldn't it be better if it were
a bit bigger and more extravagant

349
00:17:48,005 --> 00:17:49,872
to make it memorable?

350
00:17:49,872 --> 00:17:52,138
Actually, I thought the same.

351
00:17:52,138 --> 00:17:53,605
It's a once-in-a-lifetime thing,

352
00:17:53,605 --> 00:17:55,972
so I considered making it
the most luxurious and extravagant.

353
00:17:55,972 --> 00:17:56,972
Oh, and,

354
00:17:56,972 --> 00:18:00,805
I thought about holding a mini-concert.

355
00:18:00,805 --> 00:18:03,072
Huh? Mini-concert?
I was thinking the same thing.

356
00:18:03,072 --> 00:18:04,072
Huh?

357
00:18:04,072 --> 00:18:06,505
Hui Won really loves listening to music.

358
00:18:06,505 --> 00:18:07,505
Oh, really? Is that okay?

359
00:18:07,505 --> 00:18:08,605
Yeah, it's okay,

360
00:18:08,605 --> 00:18:10,805
no, I like it.

361
00:18:10,805 --> 00:18:15,105
But a performance just for one person
could be too much pressure,

362
00:18:15,105 --> 00:18:18,438
so I thought having
a small audience would be better.

363
00:18:18,438 --> 00:18:20,238
- Ordinary.
- That sounds good.

364
00:18:20,238 --> 00:18:22,405
- Huh?
- It shows preparation,

365
00:18:22,405 --> 00:18:23,605
but isn't overwhelming,

366
00:18:23,605 --> 00:18:25,672
romantic but not too much.

367
00:18:25,672 --> 00:18:27,638
- That's ordinary.
- Right?

368
00:18:27,638 --> 00:18:28,905
Wait a minute!

369
00:18:28,905 --> 00:18:31,972
- What's ordinary about that?
- Huh?

370
00:18:31,972 --> 00:18:34,338
You two seem like you could charm any woman,

371
00:18:34,338 --> 00:18:36,272
yet you have no idea
what women are really saying?

372
00:18:36,272 --> 00:18:37,872
Big and flashy is nice,

373
00:18:37,872 --> 00:18:39,305
but do you need to propose

374
00:18:39,305 --> 00:18:42,605
in front of everyone,
being the center of attention?

375
00:18:42,605 --> 00:18:45,238
No! And what's this concert thing?

376
00:18:45,238 --> 00:18:46,672
Are you throwing a festival?

377
00:18:46,672 --> 00:18:47,872
President, listen carefully.

378
00:18:47,872 --> 00:18:49,538
What you're talking about now

379
00:18:49,538 --> 00:18:51,572
isn't ordinary, it's excessive.

380
00:18:51,572 --> 00:18:53,472
It's just that in a place
with a nice atmosphere,

381
00:18:53,472 --> 00:18:55,205
when your true feelings

382
00:18:55,205 --> 00:18:57,538
meet the other's unexpectedly, bam!

383
00:18:57,538 --> 00:18:59,472
That's the proposal.

384
00:19:01,238 --> 00:19:02,272
Oh, and,

385
00:19:02,272 --> 00:19:04,905
being big and flashy only works for

386
00:19:04,905 --> 00:19:07,438
this one thing, you know?

387
00:19:08,072 --> 00:19:10,838
This is 'the more, the better', got it?

388
00:19:10,838 --> 00:19:12,572
Huh?

389
00:19:35,805 --> 00:19:37,438
The trial date is set.

390
00:19:37,438 --> 00:19:41,272
December 29th at 10 AM,
Seoul Central District Court.

391
00:19:41,272 --> 00:19:43,238
The lawyer wants to
meet once more tomorrow...

392
00:19:43,238 --> 00:19:45,738
Got it, now go out.

393
00:19:46,905 --> 00:19:48,405
- What are you doing?
- I'm sorry,

394
00:19:48,405 --> 00:19:50,638
but this is as far as I go.

395
00:20:10,405 --> 00:20:12,338
Where are you going?

396
00:20:12,338 --> 00:20:15,172
Not going to Uncle's again, are you?

397
00:20:15,838 --> 00:20:17,705
You don't think about me until the end, huh?

398
00:20:17,705 --> 00:20:19,272
It's for you.

399
00:20:19,272 --> 00:20:20,405
For us.

400
00:20:20,405 --> 00:20:22,238
No, that's your greed, Mom.

401
00:20:22,238 --> 00:20:23,605
I even quit the company because of you.

402
00:20:23,605 --> 00:20:24,905
Why did you quit there?

403
00:20:24,905 --> 00:20:26,072
Didn't I tell you?

404
00:20:26,072 --> 00:20:27,538
Taehan Liquor is yours!

405
00:20:27,538 --> 00:20:30,005
Have some sense of ownership!

406
00:20:30,005 --> 00:20:31,472
No, no, no.

407
00:20:31,472 --> 00:20:33,505
Let's use this chance to contact Grandpa

408
00:20:33,505 --> 00:20:35,238
and tell him you want management lessons.

409
00:20:35,238 --> 00:20:37,272
Grandpa will pick up your calls, right?

410
00:20:37,272 --> 00:20:38,638
Please, just stop!

411
00:20:38,638 --> 00:20:40,338
Mom, if you don't pay
for your sins this time,

412
00:20:40,338 --> 00:20:42,338
I'll just live as if I don't have a mother.

413
00:20:42,338 --> 00:20:43,705
What do you mean by that?

414
00:20:43,705 --> 00:20:45,338
How could you say that to me?

415
00:20:45,338 --> 00:20:48,005
After your dad passed, I struggled so hard

416
00:20:48,005 --> 00:20:50,085
to put you in that position!

417
00:20:50,085 --> 00:20:51,238
How could you do this?

418
00:20:51,238 --> 00:20:54,438
I clearly said I didn't need that position.

419
00:20:54,438 --> 00:20:55,972
It was you who didn't listen to me.

420
00:20:55,972 --> 00:20:58,038
Is family just about forcing
your own feelings on others?

421
00:20:58,038 --> 00:21:01,372
If that's family, I don't need you!

422
00:21:01,372 --> 00:21:03,438
Now, my family is just

423
00:21:03,438 --> 00:21:05,472
Grandma, Grandpa, and Uncle.

424
00:21:05,472 --> 00:21:07,105
Kang Se Hyeon!

425
00:21:07,105 --> 00:21:08,105
The trial is coming soon,

426
00:21:08,105 --> 00:21:09,538
so think carefully until then.

427
00:21:09,538 --> 00:21:12,638
Whether you truly did nothing wrong.

428
00:21:24,938 --> 00:21:26,672
Fine.

429
00:21:29,138 --> 00:21:30,905
Just go.

430
00:21:32,738 --> 00:21:36,805
I don't need any of you, so go!

431
00:21:52,505 --> 00:21:53,805
Huh?

432
00:21:53,805 --> 00:21:55,605
Se Hyeon?

433
00:22:07,038 --> 00:22:09,105
- Thank you.
- Why didn't you contact me?

434
00:22:09,105 --> 00:22:10,638
How would you know when I was coming back?

435
00:22:10,638 --> 00:22:13,072
I was feeling a bit stifled,
so I came out for some air.

436
00:22:13,072 --> 00:22:14,805
It's cold.

437
00:22:16,672 --> 00:22:19,205
I quit the company.

438
00:22:19,205 --> 00:22:20,872
But your internship isn't over.

439
00:22:20,872 --> 00:22:23,805
Was it because of your mother?

440
00:22:25,472 --> 00:22:26,838
Don't be like that.

441
00:22:26,838 --> 00:22:29,005
If it's because you're worried about me,

442
00:22:29,005 --> 00:22:31,605
I'm really fine.

443
00:22:31,605 --> 00:22:33,872
I already told Team Leader Bang.

444
00:22:33,872 --> 00:22:37,972
I didn't want to spend
the last month feeling guilty.

445
00:22:39,872 --> 00:22:43,505
I guess Mom still really hates Uncle.

446
00:22:43,505 --> 00:22:47,738
Though now it seems she's just
finding excuses for her actions.

447
00:22:47,738 --> 00:22:50,638
The trial is coming soon,
so don't worry too much.

448
00:22:50,638 --> 00:22:54,272
What about you, Se Hyeon?
I'm worried about you.

449
00:22:54,272 --> 00:22:57,138
I'm more worried about Uncle.

450
00:22:57,138 --> 00:22:59,605
I wish he would put down some of
the burden he carries about Dad.

451
00:22:59,605 --> 00:23:03,005
He hasn't visited Dad's columbarium
even once since the accident.

452
00:23:03,005 --> 00:23:04,872
Not even once?

453
00:23:04,872 --> 00:23:08,572
No. Anyway, he's being foolish.

454
00:23:08,572 --> 00:23:11,938
But now you are by his side,

455
00:23:11,938 --> 00:23:13,272
so I'm trying not to worry anymore.

456
00:23:13,272 --> 00:23:15,338
That's okay, right?

457
00:23:15,338 --> 00:23:17,038
Of course.

458
00:23:29,638 --> 00:23:32,572
Why can't you see that

459
00:23:32,572 --> 00:23:34,238
you're the one who betrayed our family?

460
00:23:34,238 --> 00:23:36,738
Probably, no one will
come back to you, President Han.

461
00:23:36,738 --> 00:23:39,672
I thought someone should tell you this.

462
00:23:40,738 --> 00:23:42,605
I'm sorry, but this is as far as I go.

463
00:23:42,605 --> 00:23:43,872
I don't need you!

464
00:23:43,872 --> 00:23:47,105
Now, my family is just
Grandma, Grandpa, and Uncle.

465
00:23:48,138 --> 00:23:51,038
Ah, no, no, baby.

466
00:23:51,038 --> 00:23:53,338
No.

467
00:23:53,338 --> 00:23:57,372
Kang Du Jun, this is all your fault.

468
00:23:57,372 --> 00:23:59,572
Because of you!

469
00:24:25,672 --> 00:24:27,872
Yes, Hui Won?

470
00:24:27,872 --> 00:24:29,605
A date?

471
00:24:31,805 --> 00:24:33,105
Why that face?

472
00:24:33,105 --> 00:24:34,572
Don't you want to go on a date with me?

473
00:24:34,572 --> 00:24:36,938
No, why would you say something so scary?

474
00:24:36,938 --> 00:24:38,205
I just feel bad

475
00:24:38,205 --> 00:24:40,938
since you must be tired,
and I'm making you drive.

476
00:24:40,938 --> 00:24:41,972
I told you I'm driving.

477
00:24:41,972 --> 00:24:43,505
I said earlier,

478
00:24:43,505 --> 00:24:45,872
just leave today's date to me.

479
00:24:45,872 --> 00:24:48,138
Then later, when we return,
I will drive no matter what.

480
00:24:48,138 --> 00:24:49,838
Absolutely not this.

481
00:24:49,838 --> 00:24:52,105
Okay.

482
00:24:52,105 --> 00:24:54,538
But where are we going?
We even took a day off.

483
00:24:54,538 --> 00:24:56,005
That's a secret!

484
00:24:56,005 --> 00:24:57,638
It wouldn't be fun if I told you in advance.

485
00:24:57,638 --> 00:24:59,472
Then, is there at least a hint?

486
00:24:59,472 --> 00:25:02,538
Hey! President, just trust me
and follow along.

487
00:25:02,538 --> 00:25:03,538
Ah, so cute, really cute.

488
00:25:03,538 --> 00:25:06,072
Hey! I'm not cute at all!

489
00:25:06,972 --> 00:25:08,272
[Flowers]
Welcome.

490
00:25:08,272 --> 00:25:10,205
Wait, why flowers if we're going on a date?

491
00:25:10,205 --> 00:25:12,709
It's nice, isn't it? A little mood boost.

492
00:25:12,709 --> 00:25:13,893
Oh.

493
00:25:13,893 --> 00:25:15,772
Pretty.

494
00:25:29,805 --> 00:25:31,638
Aren't they pretty?

495
00:25:31,638 --> 00:25:32,805
Why are you looking at me like that?

496
00:25:32,805 --> 00:25:34,138
Because it's beautiful.

497
00:25:34,138 --> 00:25:35,138
The flowers?

498
00:25:35,138 --> 00:25:37,138
Well, Hui Won with the flowers?

499
00:25:37,138 --> 00:25:39,405
Oh, jeez.

500
00:25:39,405 --> 00:25:41,505
Miss, please wrap these up.

501
00:25:41,505 --> 00:25:42,538
- Yes.
- Pick out more.

502
00:25:42,538 --> 00:25:43,838
President, what kind of flowers do you like?

503
00:25:43,838 --> 00:25:44,872
I like the Hui Won flower.

504
00:25:44,872 --> 00:25:46,138
Oh, jeez.

505
00:25:46,138 --> 00:25:47,938
It hurts.

506
00:25:52,505 --> 00:25:55,072
Is cake for changing the mood too?

507
00:25:55,072 --> 00:25:57,805
On such an important day,
it would feel lacking without cake.

508
00:25:57,805 --> 00:26:00,005
Important day?
Is today some special occasion?

509
00:26:00,005 --> 00:26:02,205
Is it our anniversary or something?

510
00:26:02,205 --> 00:26:04,805
It's not that, so don't worry.

511
00:26:04,805 --> 00:26:07,272
Ah, they all look delicious.

512
00:26:07,272 --> 00:26:09,005
President, what kind of cake do you like?

513
00:26:09,005 --> 00:26:10,472
I'm not really into bread or cake.

514
00:26:10,472 --> 00:26:11,838
I like whipped cream.

515
00:26:11,838 --> 00:26:13,138
Yeah?

516
00:26:13,138 --> 00:26:15,038
Well, if we live together,

517
00:26:15,038 --> 00:26:16,838
there will be more things to celebrate.

518
00:26:16,838 --> 00:26:18,038
If we live together? More?

519
00:26:18,038 --> 00:26:19,205
What else do you like?

520
00:26:19,205 --> 00:26:20,305
I have a good memory.

521
00:26:20,305 --> 00:26:22,572
You like whipped cream on cake and roses.

522
00:26:22,572 --> 00:26:24,505
Tell me if there's anything else.

523
00:26:24,505 --> 00:26:26,738
See? At times like this,
you're totally like a puppy.

524
00:26:26,738 --> 00:26:27,738
A puppy?

525
00:26:27,738 --> 00:26:28,938
That's an insult, right?

526
00:26:28,938 --> 00:26:32,138
I've heard of 'cool guy,' but a puppy?
What does that mean?

527
00:26:32,138 --> 00:26:35,772
Ugh, it means you're cute, like a puppy.

528
00:26:36,837 --> 00:26:38,638
Jeez.

529
00:26:38,638 --> 00:26:40,972
I am a bit cute, I admit.

530
00:26:42,605 --> 00:26:45,372
I'll take all the whipped cream.

531
00:26:53,205 --> 00:26:55,438
Wait, here?

532
00:26:55,438 --> 00:26:56,505
I'm sorry.

533
00:26:56,505 --> 00:27:00,005
I didn't think you'd come
if I told the truth.

534
00:27:01,738 --> 00:27:04,305
I greeted your parents,

535
00:27:04,305 --> 00:27:07,672
but I haven't met your brother.

536
00:27:07,672 --> 00:27:11,538
I lied because I wanted
to greet him in person.

537
00:27:11,538 --> 00:27:13,372
I'm sorry.

538
00:27:14,438 --> 00:27:18,305
If you're uncomfortable,
I'll go quickly alone.

539
00:27:18,305 --> 00:27:21,638
You'll wait for me, right?

540
00:27:35,472 --> 00:27:36,972
Hello.

541
00:27:36,972 --> 00:27:38,738
My name is Jang Hui Won.

542
00:27:38,738 --> 00:27:41,272
I really wanted to greet you in person.

543
00:27:41,272 --> 00:27:43,038
Because I've heard a lot

544
00:27:43,038 --> 00:27:45,205
about how great you were

545
00:27:45,205 --> 00:27:48,305
and how much you cared for your brother.

546
00:27:48,305 --> 00:27:52,905
I'll stay with your brother
to make sure you don't worry.

547
00:27:52,905 --> 00:27:55,238
Please look upon me kindly.

548
00:28:17,438 --> 00:28:20,005
I need to use the restroom.

549
00:28:20,005 --> 00:28:22,672
I'll take my time,

550
00:28:22,672 --> 00:28:26,538
so take your time too, President.

551
00:28:45,797 --> 00:28:47,365
[Late Kang Han Jun's Grave]

552
00:28:59,238 --> 00:29:00,997
[Late Kang Han Jun's Grave]

553
00:29:06,373 --> 00:29:08,357
[Late Kang Han Jun's Grave]

554
00:29:17,672 --> 00:29:19,405
Han Jun.

555
00:29:20,638 --> 00:29:22,472
Have you been well?

556
00:29:23,672 --> 00:29:26,838
I've been missing you more than usual today,

557
00:29:26,838 --> 00:29:29,205
maybe that's why I came here.

558
00:29:30,172 --> 00:29:32,805
I'm too late, aren't I?

559
00:29:32,805 --> 00:29:34,538
I'm sorry.

560
00:29:36,338 --> 00:29:39,438
I thought I didn't deserve forgiveness.

561
00:29:39,438 --> 00:29:43,338
I often wished it had been me instead.

562
00:29:44,238 --> 00:29:45,938
But, Han Jun,

563
00:29:46,938 --> 00:29:48,938
I still...

564
00:29:48,938 --> 00:29:53,372
I really tried hard to fill your absence.

565
00:29:53,372 --> 00:29:55,905
I think I messed up, Han Jun.

566
00:29:59,072 --> 00:30:00,772
I'm sorry.

567
00:30:03,805 --> 00:30:05,538
But, Han Jun,

568
00:30:07,072 --> 00:30:09,705
after sending you off like that,

569
00:30:10,472 --> 00:30:14,172
I've recently started wanting
to be happy for the first time.

570
00:30:15,905 --> 00:30:18,472
I found someone so precious

571
00:30:18,472 --> 00:30:21,172
that I want to protect her for life.

572
00:30:21,172 --> 00:30:22,705
Thanks to her,

573
00:30:22,705 --> 00:30:25,872
I found the courage to come see you today.

574
00:30:25,872 --> 00:30:28,038
So

575
00:30:28,038 --> 00:30:30,238
shameless, right?

576
00:30:30,238 --> 00:30:32,638
You'll forgive and support

577
00:30:33,838 --> 00:30:35,972
your terrible younger brother, right?

578
00:30:35,972 --> 00:30:37,672
Huh?

579
00:30:42,705 --> 00:30:44,372
Han Jun, I miss you so much.

580
00:30:44,372 --> 00:30:46,505
I miss you so much.

581
00:30:46,505 --> 00:30:49,605
I really miss you so much.

582
00:31:29,372 --> 00:31:31,072
You're back.

583
00:31:32,272 --> 00:31:34,405
Did you have a good talk with your brother?

584
00:31:34,405 --> 00:31:36,138
Yes.

585
00:31:37,438 --> 00:31:40,338
It seems like he's greeting us.

586
00:31:40,338 --> 00:31:42,038
It does.

587
00:31:47,038 --> 00:31:48,838
Thanks to you, Hui Won.

588
00:31:48,838 --> 00:31:50,538
Thank you.

589
00:31:56,772 --> 00:31:58,905
Thank you so much.

590
00:32:10,661 --> 00:32:12,581
[Will you marry me?]

591
00:32:15,938 --> 00:32:19,805
Seeing us like this reminds me
of preparing your birthday party.

592
00:32:19,805 --> 00:32:21,705
Me?

593
00:32:21,705 --> 00:32:24,572
That big birthday party
you and Hui Won threw for me?

594
00:32:24,572 --> 00:32:27,705
Yeah, we blew up balloons
all day back then too.

595
00:32:27,705 --> 00:32:31,572
Who knew I'd end up preparing
Jang Hui Won's proposal myself?

596
00:32:32,972 --> 00:32:35,972
Sounds like you still have regrets.

597
00:32:37,072 --> 00:32:40,072
Ah, no, not at all.

598
00:32:40,072 --> 00:32:42,805
If you say so. But why are you so flustered?

599
00:32:42,805 --> 00:32:45,305
Oh right, that side dish
you made back then was delicious.

600
00:32:45,305 --> 00:32:47,538
- That one? Was it good?
- Yeah.

601
00:32:47,538 --> 00:32:49,005
Just say the word anytime,

602
00:32:49,005 --> 00:32:50,038
I'll make it for you again.

603
00:32:50,038 --> 00:32:52,805
I didn't know you were
such a good cook. It's surprising.

604
00:32:52,805 --> 00:32:56,105
I told you, there's nothing I can't do.

605
00:32:57,472 --> 00:32:59,472
What are you doing after today?

606
00:32:59,472 --> 00:33:03,438
Today? Well, I don't know when this will end.

607
00:33:03,438 --> 00:33:05,138
Let's have a meal together.

608
00:33:08,538 --> 00:33:09,605
It's Christmas.

609
00:33:09,605 --> 00:33:11,738
If we go home early,
we'll just watch movies, right?

610
00:33:11,738 --> 00:33:14,738
What? Since when do you suggest eating first?

611
00:33:14,738 --> 00:33:17,138
Well, since you mention it, how about drinks

612
00:33:17,138 --> 00:33:18,372
instead of food?

613
00:33:18,372 --> 00:33:19,905
- Okay.
- Really?

614
00:33:19,905 --> 00:33:21,872
- Yeah.
- What? Who are you?

615
00:33:21,872 --> 00:33:24,572
Why are you being so easygoing today,
Cha Min Uk? What's up?

616
00:33:25,238 --> 00:33:27,405
Being with you is

617
00:33:28,172 --> 00:33:30,572
- fun.
- Same here.

618
00:33:40,709 --> 00:33:43,638
Oh.

619
00:33:43,638 --> 00:33:46,372
Seriously, Secretary Go,
you've been putting in a lot of effort.

620
00:33:46,372 --> 00:33:49,772
That's touching. Even Kang Du Jun
doesn't notice, but you noticed.

621
00:33:49,772 --> 00:33:52,705
I never thought I'd be wearing
a mascot head at my age.

622
00:33:52,705 --> 00:33:54,872
Of course, it is something I'm good at.

623
00:33:54,872 --> 00:33:57,477
Exactly, it's a relief.

624
00:33:57,477 --> 00:33:58,805
Oh.

625
00:33:58,805 --> 00:34:00,338
By the way, where did Du Jun go?

626
00:34:00,338 --> 00:34:01,838
You didn't hear?

627
00:34:01,838 --> 00:34:03,072
He said he forgot the ring.

628
00:34:03,072 --> 00:34:05,205
Yes, so he's making a quick trip home.

629
00:34:05,205 --> 00:34:09,038
Jeez, he's so high maintenance.

630
00:34:09,038 --> 00:34:10,838
Well then, I...

631
00:34:25,072 --> 00:34:27,472
I forgot the most important thing.

632
00:34:33,438 --> 00:34:34,905
I'm heading out now.

633
00:34:34,905 --> 00:34:36,638
See you later.

634
00:34:37,572 --> 00:34:39,205
[Se Hyeon]

635
00:34:40,972 --> 00:34:42,272
- Yes.
- Uncle, where are you?

636
00:34:42,272 --> 00:34:43,738
I need to talk to you for a second.

637
00:34:43,738 --> 00:34:45,438
Now?

638
00:35:02,238 --> 00:35:04,472
If it weren't for you...

639
00:35:04,472 --> 00:35:07,005
If it weren't for you...

640
00:35:07,005 --> 00:35:09,205
If it weren't for you...

641
00:35:42,538 --> 00:35:45,105
The subscriber you dialed is unavailable...

642
00:35:45,105 --> 00:35:46,738
Why isn't he answering?

643
00:35:46,738 --> 00:35:49,038
Did something happen?

644
00:35:50,105 --> 00:35:51,109
[Secretary Go]

645
00:35:55,909 --> 00:35:57,445
Ow!

646
00:35:59,238 --> 00:36:00,905
Oh, Hui Won.

647
00:36:00,905 --> 00:36:05,205
First, calm down.
I'll check with the front desk.

648
00:36:06,572 --> 00:36:07,572
President.

649
00:36:07,572 --> 00:36:09,672
Please look at me.

650
00:36:09,672 --> 00:36:12,005
My arm hurts so much.

651
00:36:12,005 --> 00:36:14,205
Please call a doctor.

652
00:36:17,938 --> 00:36:19,672
I'm sorry.

653
00:36:22,597 --> 00:36:25,509
It hurts!

654
00:36:32,672 --> 00:36:33,905
Hui Won.

655
00:36:33,905 --> 00:36:35,772
Why are you here?

656
00:36:37,372 --> 00:36:40,138
- What's wrong?
- I thought...

657
00:36:40,138 --> 00:36:43,105
I'd never see you again.

658
00:36:44,005 --> 00:36:45,272
I'm sorry.

659
00:36:45,272 --> 00:36:48,072
I'll never leave Yeol Mu and you again.

660
00:36:48,072 --> 00:36:49,972
Don't worry so much.

661
00:36:55,038 --> 00:36:56,705
Are you okay?

662
00:36:56,705 --> 00:36:57,838
You're not hurt anywhere, are you?

663
00:36:57,838 --> 00:37:00,572
Ah, I'm fine. This is nothing.

664
00:37:02,872 --> 00:37:04,905
That's a relief.

665
00:37:09,905 --> 00:37:13,505
Anyway, you really do make people worry.

666
00:37:26,053 --> 00:37:27,845
Oh.

667
00:37:28,805 --> 00:37:29,872
Se Hyeon!

668
00:37:29,872 --> 00:37:31,872
Ma'am! You can't get up so suddenly!

669
00:37:31,872 --> 00:37:33,172
Where is Se Hyeon?

670
00:37:33,172 --> 00:37:34,538
Where is Se Hyeon?

671
00:37:34,538 --> 00:37:35,538
Mom!

672
00:37:35,538 --> 00:37:37,505
- Se Hyeon!
- I'll get the doctor.

673
00:37:37,505 --> 00:37:38,938
Se Hyeon! Are you hurt anywhere?

674
00:37:38,938 --> 00:37:40,705
Are you hurt anywhere?

675
00:37:40,705 --> 00:37:42,138
I'm okay. What about you, Mom?

676
00:37:42,138 --> 00:37:44,338
Mom, are you okay?

677
00:37:44,338 --> 00:37:45,805
Why did you do that?

678
00:37:45,805 --> 00:37:48,172
Were you really trying to kill Uncle?

679
00:37:48,172 --> 00:37:49,605
I was wrong.

680
00:37:49,605 --> 00:37:52,305
How could I... how could I...

681
00:37:52,305 --> 00:37:55,638
Mom, if not for Uncle, I'd have died.

682
00:37:55,638 --> 00:37:58,572
Is that what you wanted, Mom?

683
00:38:01,038 --> 00:38:03,872
I...

684
00:38:03,872 --> 00:38:05,672
I must have been crazy.

685
00:38:05,672 --> 00:38:08,605
I must have lost my mind.

686
00:38:08,605 --> 00:38:09,938
Mom, I...

687
00:38:09,938 --> 00:38:11,338
I don't care about the company

688
00:38:11,338 --> 00:38:13,372
or being an heir, it means nothing to me.

689
00:38:13,372 --> 00:38:16,972
I just want to go to exhibitions
with you like we used to,

690
00:38:16,972 --> 00:38:19,605
pack lunches and go visit Dad,

691
00:38:19,605 --> 00:38:22,405
and just live like that.

692
00:38:22,405 --> 00:38:25,105
What happened to Dad wasn't Uncle's fault.

693
00:38:25,105 --> 00:38:26,605
You know that too, Mom.

694
00:38:26,605 --> 00:38:29,905
Uncle raised me so well.

695
00:38:29,905 --> 00:38:31,672
Now, let him go.

696
00:38:31,672 --> 00:38:34,472
Uncle deserves to be happy too.

697
00:38:34,472 --> 00:38:36,172
Mom.

698
00:38:38,805 --> 00:38:40,805
I'm sorry, Se Hyeon.

699
00:38:46,105 --> 00:38:51,438
I'm sorry, Se Hyeon. I was so wrong.

700
00:38:57,157 --> 00:38:59,438
[Late Kang Han Jun's Grave]

701
00:38:59,438 --> 00:39:01,005
You're lucky.

702
00:39:01,005 --> 00:39:03,005
You have someone who visits you faithfully.

703
00:39:03,005 --> 00:39:06,605
Even dead, you're doing better than me.

704
00:39:09,438 --> 00:39:11,405
How did I end up like this?

705
00:39:11,405 --> 00:39:13,972
I'm too ashamed to face you.

706
00:39:14,605 --> 00:39:17,138
I stopped by one last time
before paying for my sins.

707
00:39:17,138 --> 00:39:19,672
I won't be able to come for a while,

708
00:39:19,672 --> 00:39:21,705
so don't wait for me.

709
00:39:21,705 --> 00:39:23,505
Please watch over our Se Hyeon from there.

710
00:39:23,505 --> 00:39:25,381
I only

711
00:39:25,381 --> 00:39:27,605
end up hurting her.

712
00:39:34,472 --> 00:39:37,672
Yes, then let's proceed that way.

713
00:39:37,672 --> 00:39:39,372
Yes.

714
00:39:44,905 --> 00:39:46,605
Come in.

715
00:39:58,038 --> 00:39:59,472
You turned yourself in?

716
00:39:59,472 --> 00:40:02,838
I came here before going
to the police station.

717
00:40:17,772 --> 00:40:21,438
Thank you for saving Se Hyeon.

718
00:40:21,438 --> 00:40:24,572
Even though I know so well
the pain of losing someone,

719
00:40:24,572 --> 00:40:28,205
I almost killed my own daughter
with my own hands.

720
00:40:28,205 --> 00:40:32,005
If anything had happened to Se Hyeon,
I really couldn't have lived.

721
00:40:32,005 --> 00:40:34,738
I've been blaming you to save myself.

722
00:40:34,738 --> 00:40:36,372
The one I truly hate is myself,

723
00:40:36,372 --> 00:40:38,372
for doing nothing back then

724
00:40:38,372 --> 00:40:41,805
and failing to protect the baby in my womb.

725
00:40:43,638 --> 00:40:46,238
So don't blame yourself too much.

726
00:40:47,638 --> 00:40:49,872
And don't forgive me either.

727
00:41:06,372 --> 00:41:08,372
Failing to protect the baby

728
00:41:08,372 --> 00:41:11,205
isn't solely your fault, Jeong Eum.

729
00:41:11,205 --> 00:41:13,272
So please get up.

730
00:41:21,338 --> 00:41:22,772
Come to think of it,

731
00:41:22,772 --> 00:41:26,272
I also failed to give you a proper apology.

732
00:41:31,438 --> 00:41:33,972
I couldn't protect my brother that day,

733
00:41:33,972 --> 00:41:36,472
and because of that,
you lost two people you loved.

734
00:41:36,472 --> 00:41:38,238
I felt like I pushed you and Se Hyeon

735
00:41:38,238 --> 00:41:40,805
into hell with my own hands.

736
00:41:40,805 --> 00:41:42,905
I'm truly sorry.

737
00:41:45,538 --> 00:41:49,405
But the people who are left
behind have to live well.

738
00:41:49,405 --> 00:41:51,872
So please don't worry too much.

739
00:41:51,872 --> 00:41:55,205
I'll take good care of Se Hyeon.

740
00:42:19,205 --> 00:42:22,972
She asked me to tell you
that she was truly sorry.

741
00:42:22,972 --> 00:42:26,872
She felt she'd ruined our chance
at a good relationship.

742
00:42:26,872 --> 00:42:28,138
I see.

743
00:42:28,138 --> 00:42:29,805
But still, it's a relief.

744
00:42:29,805 --> 00:42:32,172
It seems everything has
finally found its place.

745
00:42:32,172 --> 00:42:33,705
You went through a lot, Hui Won.

746
00:42:33,705 --> 00:42:35,405
All because of me.

747
00:42:35,405 --> 00:42:37,005
I'm fine.

748
00:42:37,005 --> 00:42:39,738
Because you are by my side.

749
00:42:39,738 --> 00:42:45,405
Do you know what made me the saddest
after hearing about your accident?

750
00:42:45,405 --> 00:42:50,272
What if I could no longer
have this everyday life with you?

751
00:42:50,272 --> 00:42:52,605
For me,

752
00:42:52,605 --> 00:42:56,472
this moment feels like a miracle.

753
00:42:56,472 --> 00:42:58,872
You're standing before me.

754
00:42:58,872 --> 00:43:01,938
I can hear your voice,

755
00:43:02,572 --> 00:43:05,172
and I can touch you like this.

756
00:43:06,238 --> 00:43:07,405
Me too.

757
00:43:07,405 --> 00:43:09,538
It feels like a miracle to me too.

758
00:43:15,538 --> 00:43:17,738
President.

759
00:43:17,738 --> 00:43:19,505
Your hand...

760
00:43:20,838 --> 00:43:24,005
It took me such a long time
to hold your hand.

761
00:43:24,005 --> 00:43:25,705
I'm so sorry.

762
00:43:29,772 --> 00:43:31,472
Wait.

763
00:43:44,638 --> 00:43:49,638
Because it took so long, I don't ever
want to let go. Will you say yes?

764
00:43:49,638 --> 00:43:51,738
Marry me.

765
00:43:51,738 --> 00:43:53,938
Even though there are no flowers, no candles,

766
00:43:53,938 --> 00:43:56,005
not even the usual balloons,

767
00:43:56,005 --> 00:43:58,572
if I don't ask you now,
I think I'll go crazy.

768
00:44:01,238 --> 00:44:02,938
Yes.

769
00:44:03,572 --> 00:44:06,805
It's the most perfect proposal in the world.

770
00:44:39,205 --> 00:44:41,541
I'm finally getting married.

771
00:44:41,541 --> 00:44:43,013
Yeah.

772
00:44:44,172 --> 00:44:45,872
Ah, wait.

773
00:44:47,238 --> 00:44:48,272
I was cool, right?

774
00:44:48,272 --> 00:44:50,105
[One year later]

775
00:44:57,938 --> 00:44:59,772
No.

776
00:45:00,472 --> 00:45:02,205
[Guide to infant sleep hours, weaning foods]
Hungry?

777
00:45:05,285 --> 00:45:06,605
Whoa.

778
00:45:06,605 --> 00:45:08,838
Hae Rin, wait just a little bit.

779
00:45:08,838 --> 00:45:11,005
Huh? Wait just a little bit.
Daddy will be right there.

780
00:45:11,005 --> 00:45:13,372
Ah, don't cry.

781
00:45:13,372 --> 00:45:16,072
Hae Rin, let's change your diaper.

782
00:45:16,072 --> 00:45:17,125
Daddy will change the diaper.

783
00:45:17,125 --> 00:45:18,738
Ouch.

784
00:45:18,738 --> 00:45:21,138
Ah, it hurts.

785
00:45:24,772 --> 00:45:26,738
Hae Rin, Mommy's calling. It's Mommy.

786
00:45:26,738 --> 00:45:28,472
Mommy.

787
00:45:29,272 --> 00:45:31,172
- Yes.
- Just checking before going in.

788
00:45:31,172 --> 00:45:34,238
- How's Hae Rin?
- She's playing very well, so don't worry.

789
00:45:34,238 --> 00:45:37,738
Don't worry about here, honey.
Just do well with the Wonder Beer promotion.

790
00:45:37,738 --> 00:45:38,738
Okay.

791
00:45:38,738 --> 00:45:42,538
But even after a year, I'm still
not used to you calling me 'honey.'

792
00:45:42,538 --> 00:45:44,305
Why? What's wrong with 'honey'?

793
00:45:44,305 --> 00:45:46,105
It sounds great when you say it.

794
00:45:46,105 --> 00:45:47,538
But you never say it back even once.

795
00:45:47,538 --> 00:45:50,772
Why so distant with 'Du Jun'?

796
00:45:50,772 --> 00:45:52,438
I have to go in now.

797
00:45:52,438 --> 00:45:53,538
Do well.

798
00:45:53,538 --> 00:45:54,805
Congratulations on
making your dream come true.

799
00:45:54,805 --> 00:45:57,505
Thank you, honey.

800
00:45:59,938 --> 00:46:03,638
Hae Rin, Mommy called Daddy 'honey.'

801
00:46:04,933 --> 00:46:06,917
Let's go.

802
00:46:06,917 --> 00:46:08,372
Let's go.

803
00:46:08,372 --> 00:46:09,472
Manager Jang.

804
00:46:09,472 --> 00:46:10,872
Assistant Manager Cha volunteered to help.

805
00:46:10,872 --> 00:46:12,138
Huh? Min Uk?

806
00:46:12,138 --> 00:46:14,605
I heard the Sales Team is busy these days.

807
00:46:14,605 --> 00:46:17,538
Despite that busy schedule,
he volunteered to help.

808
00:46:17,538 --> 00:46:19,205
He even canceled his day off today.

809
00:46:19,205 --> 00:46:20,238
Even your day off?

810
00:46:20,238 --> 00:46:21,505
Well, uh...

811
00:46:21,505 --> 00:46:26,172
It's a beer event with your name on it.
How could the Sales Team's ace sit it out?

812
00:46:26,172 --> 00:46:27,238
Thanks, really.

813
00:46:27,238 --> 00:46:29,038
Wow, this is how you take the initiative.

814
00:46:29,038 --> 00:46:30,538
Are you aiming for Employee of the Year
two years in a row?

815
00:46:30,538 --> 00:46:33,372
Ah, compared to Team Leader Nah, I'm nothing.

816
00:46:33,372 --> 00:46:35,305
You're leading one of our company's

817
00:46:35,305 --> 00:46:37,672
[Team Leader]
key departments now.

818
00:46:37,672 --> 00:46:38,705
[Team Leader Nah In Nam]
Well, I

819
00:46:38,705 --> 00:46:40,972
kind of became team leader by accident

820
00:46:40,972 --> 00:46:43,905
[Team Leader]
while Team Leader Bang was on parental leave.

821
00:46:43,905 --> 00:46:45,072
Oh, Assistant Manager Choi,

822
00:46:45,072 --> 00:46:47,505
I heard it was your 300th day
with your boyfriend the other day?

823
00:46:47,505 --> 00:46:50,738
Is that why? You definitely
seem more relaxed.

824
00:46:50,738 --> 00:46:51,805
It's amazing.

825
00:46:51,805 --> 00:46:55,038
Actually, there's someone
even more amazing than me here.

826
00:46:55,038 --> 00:46:56,072
Tak Soo.

827
00:46:56,072 --> 00:46:57,772
- Why?
- Why Tak Soo?

828
00:46:57,772 --> 00:47:00,405
He got married just three months
after a blind date.

829
00:47:00,405 --> 00:47:01,572
Isn't that wild?

830
00:47:01,572 --> 00:47:03,138
- Really?
- Yes.

831
00:47:03,138 --> 00:47:04,638
He's so lovey-dovey.

832
00:47:04,638 --> 00:47:07,238
He even sets his wife's picture
as lock screen wallpaper.

833
00:47:07,238 --> 00:47:08,638
And he talks about her every chance he gets.

834
00:47:08,638 --> 00:47:11,872
It's terrifying.

835
00:47:11,872 --> 00:47:14,438
We're newlyweds. Please understand.

836
00:47:14,438 --> 00:47:17,005
Right, my little goofball?

837
00:47:17,005 --> 00:47:18,005
It's ten minutes before opening.

838
00:47:18,005 --> 00:47:19,005
Please get ready quickly.

839
00:47:19,005 --> 00:47:20,038
- Okay.
- Okay.

840
00:47:20,038 --> 00:47:21,772
Please get ready quickly.

841
00:47:21,772 --> 00:47:22,838
- Okay.
- Okay.

842
00:47:22,838 --> 00:47:24,505
- Shall we prepare?
- Oh, right, Manager Jang.

843
00:47:24,505 --> 00:47:25,938
What exactly does 'Wonder Beer' mean?

844
00:47:25,938 --> 00:47:28,505
Oh, right. You said you'd tell us
when we launched it.

845
00:47:28,505 --> 00:47:30,805
Ah, well...

846
00:47:30,805 --> 00:47:32,672
It's a beer named after me.

847
00:47:32,672 --> 00:47:33,738
[Jang Hui Won]
The 'Won' in Jang Hui Won.

848
00:47:33,738 --> 00:47:36,805
[Wonder: amazing]
And adding 'Wonder,' which means 'amazing'.

849
00:47:36,805 --> 00:47:37,938
[Jang Hui Won and Wonder]
Made by Jang Hui Won,

850
00:47:37,938 --> 00:47:39,138
amazing and wondrous,

851
00:47:39,138 --> 00:47:41,138
Wonder Beer!

852
00:47:46,738 --> 00:47:48,605
Ah, okay!

853
00:47:48,605 --> 00:47:50,605
So when I say 'Wonder Beer,'

854
00:47:50,605 --> 00:47:52,705
say, 'For wonderful success!'

855
00:47:52,705 --> 00:47:54,005
Ah, that's a bit...

856
00:47:54,005 --> 00:47:56,638
Why make us do something so cheesy?

857
00:47:56,638 --> 00:47:58,805
That's a little too cringey.
Please, not that.

858
00:47:58,805 --> 00:48:00,672
Hey, everyone, put your hands together.

859
00:48:00,672 --> 00:48:01,738
Okay.

860
00:48:01,738 --> 00:48:03,138
Team Leader?

861
00:48:03,138 --> 00:48:05,238
Oh, what?

862
00:48:05,238 --> 00:48:06,272
Are they twins?

863
00:48:06,272 --> 00:48:07,405
They're not twins.

864
00:48:07,405 --> 00:48:09,438
They'll be out soon.

865
00:48:09,438 --> 00:48:11,405
What? Did I come to a place I shouldn't?

866
00:48:11,405 --> 00:48:12,805
What are you doing? Hurry up
and put your hands together.

867
00:48:12,805 --> 00:48:14,538
- Up, up!
- Hurry!

868
00:48:15,538 --> 00:48:17,138
Manager Jang, go.

869
00:48:17,138 --> 00:48:18,272
For Wonder Beer's...

870
00:48:18,272 --> 00:48:22,672
- Wonderful success!
- Wonderful success!

871
00:48:22,672 --> 00:48:25,605
[Wonder Beer]

872
00:48:28,293 --> 00:48:30,105
[The Wonder Zone,
The Flavor Zone, The Mother Zone]

873
00:48:30,105 --> 00:48:31,105
[Wonder Beer, enjoyed with peace of mind,
even by pregnant women]

874
00:48:31,105 --> 00:48:33,638
This isn't just any ordinary
non-alcoholic beer.

875
00:48:33,638 --> 00:48:35,005
It retains the full flavor of beer,

876
00:48:35,005 --> 00:48:36,072
but with zero alcohol!

877
00:48:36,072 --> 00:48:38,905
One sip is worth more than
a hundred words. Please try it.

878
00:48:38,905 --> 00:48:40,605
But it really has no alcohol?

879
00:48:40,605 --> 00:48:43,538
It's truly safe for pregnant women, right?

880
00:48:43,538 --> 00:48:45,705
Of course, absolutely.

881
00:48:45,705 --> 00:48:47,372
Want me to show you?

882
00:48:47,372 --> 00:48:48,453
Yes.

883
00:48:48,453 --> 00:48:51,269
Oh.

884
00:48:52,709 --> 00:48:55,338
Wow, it's really refreshing.

885
00:48:55,338 --> 00:48:56,672
- It's so delicious.
- Right?

886
00:48:56,672 --> 00:48:58,138
I'll pour you each a glass.

887
00:48:58,138 --> 00:48:59,372
Because it's non-alcoholic,

888
00:48:59,372 --> 00:49:01,338
you can drink as much as
you want without worry.

889
00:49:01,338 --> 00:49:04,372
And what's even better is
it is low in calories.

890
00:49:04,372 --> 00:49:05,972
Assistant Manager?

891
00:49:05,972 --> 00:49:07,205
Would you like to try a glass?

892
00:49:07,205 --> 00:49:11,838
It's non-alcoholic but has the same crispness
and carbonation as a regular lager.

893
00:49:11,838 --> 00:49:13,538
- The taste is excellent too.
- Thank you.

894
00:49:13,538 --> 00:49:15,838
A friend of mine who's passionate
about beer made it.

895
00:49:15,838 --> 00:49:17,705
Please give it a try.

896
00:49:18,338 --> 00:49:20,538
Could I also have a sip?

897
00:49:20,538 --> 00:49:22,938
Of course, here.

898
00:49:23,805 --> 00:49:25,438
Mom.

899
00:49:25,438 --> 00:49:26,738
What brings you here?

900
00:49:26,738 --> 00:49:31,072
Didn't you want to try the beer
with me first when it launched?

901
00:49:31,072 --> 00:49:33,472
Did you see the video?

902
00:49:33,472 --> 00:49:34,638
You spoke really well.

903
00:49:34,638 --> 00:49:37,005
It made me curious
enough to come all the way here.

904
00:49:37,005 --> 00:49:39,472
You should've told me you were coming.

905
00:49:39,472 --> 00:49:40,838
I would've invited you properly.

906
00:49:40,838 --> 00:49:42,605
I knew you were busy, why bother?

907
00:49:42,605 --> 00:49:44,205
Should I try that one?

908
00:49:44,205 --> 00:49:46,138
Yes, here.

909
00:49:50,972 --> 00:49:53,338
- Oh.
- How is it?

910
00:49:53,338 --> 00:49:55,972
Not bad. Better than regular beer.

911
00:49:55,972 --> 00:49:58,338
Really? Then drink this
when you crave alcohol.

912
00:49:58,338 --> 00:50:03,438
Hey, people drink alcohol to get drunk.
This isn't alcohol.

913
00:50:03,438 --> 00:50:05,905
But you get drunk three times a week already.
You want to get even drunker?

914
00:50:05,905 --> 00:50:07,305
Drink the non-alcoholic one.

915
00:50:07,305 --> 00:50:09,305
That way you can drink with me.

916
00:50:09,305 --> 00:50:12,072
You're not getting any younger,
so think about your health.

917
00:50:12,072 --> 00:50:14,305
Okay, stop nagging.

918
00:50:14,305 --> 00:50:15,438
Hey, why don't you say it louder?

919
00:50:15,438 --> 00:50:17,272
I'm worried about you,

920
00:50:17,272 --> 00:50:18,972
and you're on a diet lately.

921
00:50:18,972 --> 00:50:21,405
This one's low in calories,
so it's great for you.

922
00:50:21,405 --> 00:50:23,205
So just once. Try just one more sip.

923
00:50:23,205 --> 00:50:24,805
Does it have barley in it? Really?

924
00:50:24,805 --> 00:50:26,272
- It's just like beer.
- Please give it a taste before you go.

925
00:50:26,272 --> 00:50:28,172
Delicious, right?

926
00:50:28,172 --> 00:50:30,305
I gave it my all today.

927
00:50:30,305 --> 00:50:32,238
I can't even move a finger.

928
00:50:32,238 --> 00:50:35,072
Agreed. I'm not taking the bus today,
I'm taking a taxi home.

929
00:50:35,072 --> 00:50:37,538
Huh? Now that I think about it,
Se Hyeon isn't here today.

930
00:50:37,538 --> 00:50:39,705
Oh, right. How is Se Hyeon doing?

931
00:50:39,705 --> 00:50:42,038
I thought she'd be the first
to come congratulate Manager Jang.

932
00:50:42,038 --> 00:50:43,772
She said she's taking
a short trip these days.

933
00:50:43,772 --> 00:50:46,138
She said she misses everyone, actually.

934
00:50:46,138 --> 00:50:47,805
If she misses us, tell her to come see us.

935
00:50:47,805 --> 00:50:49,805
It's not like we'd pick on her if she came.

936
00:50:49,805 --> 00:50:53,138
I'll let her know Team Leader Bang
misses her the most.

937
00:50:53,138 --> 00:50:54,138
Okay.

938
00:50:54,138 --> 00:50:55,172
Oh, jeez.

939
00:50:55,172 --> 00:50:57,189
Honey!

940
00:50:57,189 --> 00:50:59,572
- Oh.
- Oh dear, honey.

941
00:50:59,572 --> 00:51:02,472
Oh my, your back.

942
00:51:02,472 --> 00:51:04,549
- My feet, my feet!
- I told you not to come alone,

943
00:51:04,549 --> 00:51:05,838
so why did you come alone?

944
00:51:05,838 --> 00:51:08,372
I was worried about you.

945
00:51:08,372 --> 00:51:11,605
Yeah, I was just excited to see
my teammates after so long.

946
00:51:11,605 --> 00:51:14,372
I'm so happy you came, honey.

947
00:51:14,372 --> 00:51:17,872
Oh, well.

948
00:51:17,872 --> 00:51:20,372
Oh, hello.

949
00:51:21,605 --> 00:51:23,905
Don't move even one meter away from me.

950
00:51:23,905 --> 00:51:26,372
No, not even one centimeter, okay?

951
00:51:26,372 --> 00:51:29,838
Okay, then tonight let's make it intense.

952
00:51:29,838 --> 00:51:32,172
Oh my, how embarrassing.

953
00:51:33,305 --> 00:51:36,472
I still can't forget when they
told us they were dating.

954
00:51:36,472 --> 00:51:39,038
I sometimes dream of it,
and I wake up startled every time.

955
00:51:39,038 --> 00:51:40,538
I'm afraid I'll dream of it tonight.

956
00:51:40,538 --> 00:51:44,172
I haven't even eaten today,
but my stomach feels upset.

957
00:51:44,172 --> 00:51:47,605
Manager Jang, you've had the baby
and launched the beer.

958
00:51:47,605 --> 00:51:48,705
Aren't you going to hold
the wedding ceremony?

959
00:51:48,705 --> 00:51:52,805
We were actually trying to set a date
right after the birth, but it's not easy.

960
00:51:52,805 --> 00:51:54,605
Has the President said anything?

961
00:51:54,605 --> 00:51:56,638
Lately, he's busier than I am
taking care of the baby.

962
00:51:56,638 --> 00:51:58,338
Manager Jang really
does things in reverse, huh?

963
00:51:58,338 --> 00:52:03,038
Baby first, wedding later, soon it'll be
the first birthday before the ceremony, huh?

964
00:52:03,038 --> 00:52:04,072
Doesn't that bother you?

965
00:52:04,072 --> 00:52:07,072
My wife says she could give up
everything else, but not the wedding.

966
00:52:07,072 --> 00:52:11,205
For me, living well together is
more important than the wedding.

967
00:52:11,205 --> 00:52:13,838
- Right.
- In that case, I'll head out first.

968
00:52:13,838 --> 00:52:16,938
I have to get my husband settled
after putting the baby to bed.

969
00:52:18,038 --> 00:52:19,905
What?

970
00:52:21,338 --> 00:52:23,405
- Oh, thanks for your hard work.
- I'm so jealous.

971
00:52:23,405 --> 00:52:25,405
Oh, seriously.

972
00:52:25,405 --> 00:52:27,438
- Here.
- What is it?

973
00:52:27,438 --> 00:52:29,438
Mi Ran and I bought a coat for Hae Rin.

974
00:52:29,438 --> 00:52:30,672
Again?

975
00:52:30,672 --> 00:52:34,305
You bought her tons of
thermal underwear last time.

976
00:52:34,305 --> 00:52:35,972
Thanks.

977
00:52:35,972 --> 00:52:39,072
By the way, did you two fight
again after that?

978
00:52:39,072 --> 00:52:41,072
Why? Did Mi Ran call again?

979
00:52:41,072 --> 00:52:43,005
Gosh, Hwang Mi Ran.

980
00:52:43,005 --> 00:52:46,505
Back then she couldn't even say
she liked you to me and just agonized.

981
00:52:46,505 --> 00:52:48,338
These days, it's nothing but talk about you.

982
00:52:48,338 --> 00:52:50,372
Loves you to death one minute,
hates you the next.

983
00:52:50,372 --> 00:52:53,372
Sorry. I should be nicer to her.

984
00:52:53,372 --> 00:52:54,405
I've got my own guilt, after all.

985
00:52:54,405 --> 00:52:59,072
Yeah, to appease Mi Ran, you just
have to be extra sweet to her, got it?

986
00:52:59,072 --> 00:53:00,738
- Okay.
- But it's nice to see.

987
00:53:00,738 --> 00:53:04,438
Before, you were always
taking care of others and giving,

988
00:53:04,438 --> 00:53:06,938
but there was nothing left for yourself.

989
00:53:06,938 --> 00:53:11,872
I used to think you should know the joy
of receiving too, not just giving.

990
00:53:11,872 --> 00:53:14,705
Seems like you're doing that lately.

991
00:53:15,338 --> 00:53:17,438
It makes me even happier.

992
00:53:19,105 --> 00:53:20,272
I'm glad

993
00:53:20,272 --> 00:53:23,838
you look happy, even though you're busy.

994
00:53:23,838 --> 00:53:27,038
I definitely sleep less,
and I'm busier than before,

995
00:53:27,038 --> 00:53:29,538
but having a baby is incredibly healing.

996
00:53:29,538 --> 00:53:32,472
In the morning, when I try to leave
for work after putting her down,

997
00:53:32,472 --> 00:53:33,838
I really tear up.

998
00:53:33,838 --> 00:53:36,605
Ah, working moms are really amazing.

999
00:53:36,605 --> 00:53:39,505
But you can rest a bit on weekends, right?

1000
00:53:39,505 --> 00:53:41,905
Hey, moms don't get weekends.

1001
00:53:41,905 --> 00:53:45,238
I have to play even harder on weekends
to make up for my time away during the week.

1002
00:53:45,238 --> 00:53:46,905
That's true.

1003
00:53:46,905 --> 00:53:49,772
I'll stop by with Mi Ran
some time to see Hae Rin.

1004
00:53:49,772 --> 00:53:51,105
Give my regards to your husband, too.

1005
00:53:51,105 --> 00:53:53,905
Sure, he said you guys are always welcome.

1006
00:53:53,905 --> 00:53:55,472
Just say the word.

1007
00:53:55,472 --> 00:53:57,172
Okay.

1008
00:54:06,438 --> 00:54:07,493
[Congratulations on launching Wonder Beer]

1009
00:54:09,172 --> 00:54:11,397
[You don't just make beer, you make art]

1010
00:54:12,638 --> 00:54:14,805
What is this, seriously?

1011
00:55:01,372 --> 00:55:04,105
Did the promotion go well?

1012
00:55:05,272 --> 00:55:06,872
Thanks to you.

1013
00:55:06,872 --> 00:55:08,872
You worked hard.

1014
00:55:08,872 --> 00:55:11,172
Well done, wifey.

1015
00:55:16,238 --> 00:55:19,005
But why do you look not so happy?

1016
00:55:20,205 --> 00:55:22,105
Because I'm too happy.

1017
00:55:22,105 --> 00:55:24,038
If it weren't for you, Du Jun,

1018
00:55:24,038 --> 00:55:27,672
I wouldn't have this kind of happiness.

1019
00:55:29,105 --> 00:55:32,738
But even in this moment,
you're calling me 'Du Jun' again?

1020
00:55:34,772 --> 00:55:36,505
Huh?

1021
00:55:47,005 --> 00:55:51,045
Should we put the baby to sleep first
and then finish what we were doing?

1022
00:55:51,045 --> 00:55:52,105
Alright.

1023
00:55:52,105 --> 00:55:53,205
I'll make the formula first.

1024
00:55:53,205 --> 00:55:55,238
I'll handle the diaper.

1025
00:55:55,238 --> 00:55:57,205
- Oh, gosh.
- Oh dear.

1026
00:56:01,505 --> 00:56:03,572
Oh, Hae Rin.

1027
00:56:03,572 --> 00:56:05,305
Grandma's here.

1028
00:56:05,305 --> 00:56:09,005
Oh my, oh my.

1029
00:56:09,005 --> 00:56:12,238
Oh dear, have you been good?

1030
00:56:12,938 --> 00:56:14,438
Oh my, so pretty.

1031
00:56:14,438 --> 00:56:17,372
Wow, you were so tough on your daughter,

1032
00:56:17,372 --> 00:56:18,838
but the granddaughter's adorable, huh?

1033
00:56:18,838 --> 00:56:20,738
What's with that all of a sudden?

1034
00:56:20,738 --> 00:56:23,305
What have you been doing
all this time? Why aren't you ready?

1035
00:56:23,305 --> 00:56:25,038
I was busy watching Hae Rin.

1036
00:56:25,038 --> 00:56:26,405
But will you be okay on your own?

1037
00:56:26,405 --> 00:56:28,805
Or should we come back
and have dinner together?

1038
00:56:28,805 --> 00:56:30,605
You said it's a date after so long.

1039
00:56:30,605 --> 00:56:33,072
I'm going to relax with Hae Rin.

1040
00:56:33,072 --> 00:56:35,272
Don't worry about me,
and come back late. Very late.

1041
00:56:35,272 --> 00:56:36,405
What's gotten into you?

1042
00:56:36,405 --> 00:56:38,605
Did he give you a generous
allowance or something?

1043
00:56:38,605 --> 00:56:41,472
Go get ready.
You said he's waiting downstairs.

1044
00:56:41,472 --> 00:56:43,205
Okay.

1045
00:56:46,638 --> 00:56:48,338
- Mom.
- Huh?

1046
00:56:48,338 --> 00:56:49,872
Thanks for watching the baby.

1047
00:56:49,872 --> 00:56:53,205
Call me often. You've been busy lately.

1048
00:56:53,205 --> 00:56:55,905
This is when you get your mom's help.

1049
00:56:58,405 --> 00:57:01,872
Hae Rin, have you been doing well?

1050
00:57:01,872 --> 00:57:03,738
Here, look at this.

1051
00:57:03,738 --> 00:57:06,638
But is it really okay to leave Hae Rin
with your mom and be out like this?

1052
00:57:06,638 --> 00:57:10,181
Yeah, she told us not to worry
and just have fun.

1053
00:57:10,181 --> 00:57:11,938
Oh, it's a fish-shaped bun!

1054
00:57:11,938 --> 00:57:13,638
Do you want some?

1055
00:57:14,838 --> 00:57:16,305
- Hello.
- Welcome.

1056
00:57:16,305 --> 00:57:17,905
We'll take four fish-shaped buns.

1057
00:57:17,905 --> 00:57:19,638
Okay.

1058
00:57:20,538 --> 00:57:22,305
See if it's too hot.

1059
00:57:25,338 --> 00:57:26,472
How is it? Is it good?

1060
00:57:26,472 --> 00:57:28,072
Yeah.

1061
00:57:28,072 --> 00:57:30,038
Du Jun, you should try some too.

1062
00:57:31,805 --> 00:57:33,138
Huh? It's not red bean?

1063
00:57:33,138 --> 00:57:34,338
Red bean is the classic filling
for fish-shaped buns.

1064
00:57:34,338 --> 00:57:38,138
Come on, red bean's just the standard.
Custard filling is amazing.

1065
00:57:38,138 --> 00:57:39,205
Come on.

1066
00:57:39,205 --> 00:57:41,705
So, do you eat it
from the head or from the tail?

1067
00:57:41,705 --> 00:57:45,272
Then let's say it at the same time on three.

1068
00:57:45,272 --> 00:57:47,838
- Okay.
- One, two, three.

1069
00:57:47,838 --> 00:57:48,872
- Head.
- Tail.

1070
00:57:48,872 --> 00:57:50,138
You clearly don't know how to eat one.

1071
00:57:50,138 --> 00:57:52,805
It's all about feeling
that crunch in the tail first.

1072
00:57:52,805 --> 00:57:54,005
Haven't you heard
'the head is the best part of a fish'?

1073
00:57:54,005 --> 00:57:55,772
The head's the best part
for fish-shaped buns.

1074
00:57:55,772 --> 00:57:58,505
Gosh, why are you so passionate
about a fish-shaped bun?

1075
00:57:58,505 --> 00:58:01,438
Coming from the person trying
to teach me about fish-shaped buns?

1076
00:58:01,438 --> 00:58:04,405
Lately, I've been counting down
to winter just for fish-shaped buns.

1077
00:58:04,405 --> 00:58:07,172
Hui Won, you've completely changed
my taste buds this past year.

1078
00:58:07,172 --> 00:58:08,738
- No way.
- It's true.

1079
00:58:08,738 --> 00:58:09,838
Ah, since we're on the topic.

1080
00:58:09,838 --> 00:58:12,372
Sir, I'd like to hire you.

1081
00:58:12,372 --> 00:58:13,938
How about selling

1082
00:58:13,938 --> 00:58:16,038
in front of my house all year round
through all four seasons?

1083
00:58:16,038 --> 00:58:18,725
I'll pay you a very generous salary.

1084
00:58:18,725 --> 00:58:19,738
Oh.

1085
00:58:19,738 --> 00:58:21,172
He's just joking.

1086
00:58:21,172 --> 00:58:22,272
I'm serious.

1087
00:58:22,272 --> 00:58:23,705
About 20 million won after taxes.

1088
00:58:23,705 --> 00:58:24,805
Deal.

1089
00:58:24,805 --> 00:58:25,838
How about this?

1090
00:58:25,838 --> 00:58:27,272
Oh, it messes up my hair.

1091
00:58:27,272 --> 00:58:29,472
That's not a couple thing.

1092
00:58:29,472 --> 00:58:31,238
It suits you.

1093
00:58:37,538 --> 00:58:41,605
I didn't expect it at all,
but today felt like a complete gift.

1094
00:58:41,605 --> 00:58:44,272
Is there anywhere else
you'd like to go later?

1095
00:58:44,997 --> 00:58:50,538
Oh, I'd like to go back to
that Itaewon pub where we first met.

1096
00:58:50,538 --> 00:58:52,138
The Itaewon pub?

1097
00:58:52,138 --> 00:58:54,038
Don't tell me you don't remember it.

1098
00:58:54,038 --> 00:58:56,005
But that's not where we first met.

1099
00:58:56,005 --> 00:58:58,605
What do you mean, not where we first met?

1100
00:58:58,605 --> 00:59:01,105
Huh? Why is there a church here?

1101
00:59:01,105 --> 00:59:02,772
Shall we go in? I'm bored.

1102
00:59:02,772 --> 00:59:04,138
- Huh?
- Let's go in.

1103
00:59:04,138 --> 00:59:05,838
Come this way.

1104
00:59:43,605 --> 00:59:46,172
Doesn't it suit you perfectly?
You look so beautiful.

1105
00:59:46,172 --> 00:59:47,738
When did you prepare all this?

1106
00:59:47,738 --> 00:59:50,872
I wanted to throw you a huge wedding
after the baby was born,

1107
00:59:50,872 --> 00:59:52,438
but it kept getting delayed.

1108
00:59:52,438 --> 00:59:55,205
It was postponed because I was busy.

1109
00:59:55,838 --> 00:59:58,038
Then, shall we practice
the wedding ceremony in advance?

1110
00:59:58,038 --> 00:59:59,738
Huh?

1111
01:00:07,205 --> 01:00:12,038
Even if it's just practice, you need
a veil for a wedding, right?

1112
01:00:21,238 --> 01:00:22,838
Blessings to you both.

1113
01:00:22,838 --> 01:00:25,138
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

1114
01:00:27,272 --> 01:00:29,538
By the way, you don't seem
to remember very well,

1115
01:00:29,538 --> 01:00:33,038
but our first meeting wasn't
at an Itaewon pub, but a hotel party hall.

1116
01:00:33,038 --> 01:00:37,338
You showed up with red hair
and in sharp heels and suddenly said to me,

1117
01:00:37,338 --> 01:00:38,437
'Excuse me.'

1118
01:00:38,437 --> 01:00:39,872
Could you back me up?

1119
01:00:39,872 --> 01:00:42,472
Honey, the atmosphere here is amazing.

1120
01:00:42,472 --> 01:00:44,238
Then, that person back then...

1121
01:00:44,238 --> 01:00:45,238
You think that's all?

1122
01:00:45,238 --> 01:00:47,772
The woman who cried in the rain.

1123
01:00:47,772 --> 01:00:49,238
Hey! Come out here!

1124
01:00:49,238 --> 01:00:51,272
How could you do this to me, huh?

1125
01:00:51,272 --> 01:00:52,972
What did I do wrong?

1126
01:00:52,972 --> 01:00:54,838
Why are you treating me like this?

1127
01:00:54,838 --> 01:00:56,638
I don't know if you were drunk or dumped,

1128
01:00:56,638 --> 01:00:59,838
but you were a mess, crying, sniffling,
and you even took my check.

1129
01:00:59,838 --> 01:01:03,205
That... 1 million won.

1130
01:01:03,205 --> 01:01:06,238
No, please forget about that.

1131
01:01:06,238 --> 01:01:10,805
Why? It's a precious memory
I want to cherish forever.

1132
01:01:14,538 --> 01:01:17,405
But have I ever said this before?

1133
01:01:21,205 --> 01:01:22,972
That I love you.

1134
01:01:25,305 --> 01:01:28,172
I love you, Jang Hui Won.

1135
01:01:31,138 --> 01:01:32,872
Me too.

1136
01:01:34,272 --> 01:01:36,438
I love you too.

1137
01:02:08,472 --> 01:02:09,541
[Celebrating Hae Rin's First Birthday]

1138
01:02:10,938 --> 01:02:12,165
[First Birthday]

1139
01:02:14,629 --> 01:02:15,781
[Celebrating Hae Rin's First Birthday]

1140
01:02:19,405 --> 01:02:22,672
Mom, don't worry. I told you she invited you.

1141
01:02:22,672 --> 01:02:24,538
Come on, smile.

1142
01:02:25,205 --> 01:02:26,372
Grandma.

1143
01:02:26,372 --> 01:02:28,105
Huh?

1144
01:02:29,272 --> 01:02:31,672
I'm here.

1145
01:02:34,505 --> 01:02:36,105
You're here.

1146
01:02:36,105 --> 01:02:38,405
Come on in.

1147
01:02:38,405 --> 01:02:40,372
You shouldn't miss an occasion like this.

1148
01:02:40,372 --> 01:02:42,305
You're family too.

1149
01:02:42,305 --> 01:02:43,905
[Family Section]

1150
01:02:43,905 --> 01:02:46,605
Yeah, you've worked hard.

1151
01:02:46,605 --> 01:02:48,338
Let's sit down.

1152
01:02:52,438 --> 01:02:53,738
It's been a while.

1153
01:02:53,738 --> 01:02:56,072
- I'm sorry.
- You haven't even shown your face.

1154
01:02:56,072 --> 01:02:58,972
Sorry, I've been busy.

1155
01:02:58,972 --> 01:03:00,805
Thank you.

1156
01:03:01,505 --> 01:03:02,838
- Congratulations.
- Thank you.

1157
01:03:02,838 --> 01:03:05,138
- Thank you.
- Jang Hui Won.

1158
01:03:05,138 --> 01:03:07,072
Hey guys.

1159
01:03:07,072 --> 01:03:09,538
- Where's Hae Rin?
- Ah, she's taking a short nap.

1160
01:03:09,538 --> 01:03:11,872
[Celebrating Hae Rin's First Birthday]
Hey, you worked hard preparing.

1161
01:03:11,872 --> 01:03:14,638
You really worked hard raising her.

1162
01:03:14,638 --> 01:03:16,205
Du Jun did most of it, really.

1163
01:03:16,205 --> 01:03:17,405
Thank you for coming.

1164
01:03:17,405 --> 01:03:18,805
Of course, I had to come.

1165
01:03:18,805 --> 01:03:21,305
This first birthday party is more important
than your wedding.

1166
01:03:21,305 --> 01:03:23,072
You must be hungry. Go inside and sit down.

1167
01:03:23,072 --> 01:03:24,105
Go on in.

1168
01:03:24,105 --> 01:03:26,372
- Congratulations.
- Thank you.

1169
01:03:27,438 --> 01:03:29,572
Manager.

1170
01:03:29,572 --> 01:03:32,572
Oh my goodness,
whose first birthday party is this beautiful?

1171
01:03:32,572 --> 01:03:33,605
Wow, Manager Jang.

1172
01:03:33,605 --> 01:03:35,938
I almost didn't recognize you
dressed like that. Congratulations.

1173
01:03:35,938 --> 01:03:37,438
President, congratulations.

1174
01:03:37,438 --> 01:03:39,005
- Congratulations.
- Thank you.

1175
01:03:39,005 --> 01:03:40,372
Thank you for coming.

1176
01:03:40,372 --> 01:03:42,105
We're honored you invited us.

1177
01:03:42,105 --> 01:03:45,372
It feels different seeing each other
outside the office like this.

1178
01:03:45,372 --> 01:03:47,572
By the way, where's Team Leader Bang?

1179
01:03:47,572 --> 01:03:48,672
I'm here!

1180
01:03:48,672 --> 01:03:49,972
Oh dear, careful, careful.

1181
01:03:49,972 --> 01:03:52,538
Where in the world is there a baby
this big and beautiful?

1182
01:03:52,538 --> 01:03:54,638
And I get to see her every day.

1183
01:03:54,638 --> 01:03:56,372
- Those two are really close.
- My dear baby!

1184
01:03:56,372 --> 01:03:57,605
I never get tired of seeing you.

1185
01:03:57,605 --> 01:03:58,605
Hello.

1186
01:03:58,605 --> 01:04:02,205
- So cute!
- So adorable.

1187
01:04:02,205 --> 01:04:04,505
Wait, isn't that Se Hyeon over there?

1188
01:04:04,505 --> 01:04:05,838
Yeah, why is Se Hyeon there?

1189
01:04:05,838 --> 01:04:07,472
Maybe Se Hyeon arrived earlier.

1190
01:04:07,472 --> 01:04:09,105
That's not it, that area is

1191
01:04:09,105 --> 01:04:10,272
the family section.

1192
01:04:10,272 --> 01:04:11,685
Why in the family section?

1193
01:04:11,685 --> 01:04:13,005
- Oh?
- Oh.

1194
01:04:13,005 --> 01:04:14,872
Hello.

1195
01:04:14,872 --> 01:04:16,138
Have you been well?

1196
01:04:16,138 --> 01:04:17,738
How have you been?

1197
01:04:17,738 --> 01:04:19,638
Manager, I heard you became a team leader.

1198
01:04:19,638 --> 01:04:22,338
Oh, I just kind of ended up as team leader.

1199
01:04:22,338 --> 01:04:23,338
Here we go again.

1200
01:04:23,338 --> 01:04:25,438
And you probably didn't know,
but she's my niece.

1201
01:04:25,438 --> 01:04:27,013
What?

1202
01:04:27,013 --> 01:04:28,072
What?

1203
01:04:28,072 --> 01:04:29,705
Oh, Ms. Se Hyeon, hello.

1204
01:04:29,705 --> 01:04:32,672
No, please sit down. No need for this.

1205
01:04:32,672 --> 01:04:34,872
Please, make yourself comfortable.

1206
01:04:34,872 --> 01:04:35,872
Sit down quickly.

1207
01:04:35,872 --> 01:04:39,072
Why didn't you say you're his niece?

1208
01:04:39,072 --> 01:04:40,705
- Huh? Secretary Go?
- You're here.

1209
01:04:40,705 --> 01:04:42,438
Oh, yes.

1210
01:04:46,277 --> 01:04:48,838
- Baby!
- Hi baby!

1211
01:04:48,838 --> 01:04:50,972
- Daddy's here, Daddy.
- Daddy.

1212
01:04:50,972 --> 01:04:52,938
Daddy's here.

1213
01:04:52,938 --> 01:04:54,472
Peekaboo!

1214
01:04:54,472 --> 01:04:55,572
Hello.

1215
01:04:55,572 --> 01:04:57,338
Oh my, how pretty.

1216
01:04:58,238 --> 01:05:00,972
A year ago, when I saw
two lines on the pregnancy test stick,

1217
01:05:00,972 --> 01:05:03,572
it felt like the world stopped.

1218
01:05:03,572 --> 01:05:05,738
[SRMR Obstetrics and Gynecology Clinic]
I wasn't ready yet.

1219
01:05:05,738 --> 01:05:08,705
I hadn't planned on marriage
or a child in this lifetime.

1220
01:05:08,705 --> 01:05:10,838
I was completely overwhelmed.

1221
01:05:10,838 --> 01:05:13,638
Because it was the biggest
variable in my life.

1222
01:05:13,638 --> 01:05:16,372
But I've never been alone.

1223
01:05:26,005 --> 01:05:27,838
I like you.

1224
01:05:45,405 --> 01:05:48,438
There is someone by my side
who loves me consistently,

1225
01:05:48,438 --> 01:05:51,372
and I have many friends cheering me on.

1226
01:06:56,005 --> 01:06:58,438
Looking back, we sometimes hurt each other,

1227
01:06:58,438 --> 01:07:02,138
forgave, and held hands again,

1228
01:07:02,138 --> 01:07:05,238
and learned how to become a real family.

1229
01:07:06,372 --> 01:07:10,372
As this child grows up, so do I.

1230
01:07:12,405 --> 01:07:15,372
I've learned how to love, how to forgive,

1231
01:07:15,372 --> 01:07:18,305
and how to be happy.

1232
01:07:28,905 --> 01:07:30,505
Having a baby isn't just

1233
01:07:30,505 --> 01:07:33,305
about a new life coming into the world,

1234
01:07:33,305 --> 01:07:36,438
it means all of our lives change.

1235
01:07:48,338 --> 01:07:50,572
And that variable

1236
01:07:50,572 --> 01:07:53,472
turns out to be the best gift of my life.

1237
01:07:53,472 --> 01:07:56,038
Alright, we'll take the photo now.

1238
01:07:56,772 --> 01:07:59,005
Everyone's in a good mood today, right?

1239
01:07:59,005 --> 01:08:00,272
- Yes.
- Yes.

1240
01:08:00,272 --> 01:08:01,872
Just a bigger smile, please.

1241
01:08:01,872 --> 01:08:04,005
Okay, here we go.

1242
01:08:04,005 --> 01:08:06,772
One, two!
